  "text": "Stack clash protection in GCC spans these key files: (1) gcc/config/i386/i386.cc contains x86_64-specific stack clash probing via `get_probe_interval()` (line 6936) which checks `flag_stack_clash_protection`, and `dump_stack_clash_frame_info()` calls at lines 8229-8403 implementing inline/loop probe strategies. (2) gcc/explow.cc implements the generic stack clash expansion with `anti_adjust_stack_and_probe_stack_clash()` (line 2072) for stack-clash-specific probing and `anti_adjust_stack_and_probe()` (line 2201) for general probing. (3) gcc/target.def declares the `TARGET_STACK_CLASH_PROTECTION_ALLOCA_PROBE_RANGE` target hook via DEFHOOK at line 6534, with default implementation in gcc/targhooks.cc (`default_stack_clash_protection_alloca_probe_range`, line 2747) and its prototype in gcc/targhooks.h (line 305). (4) The test file gcc/testsuite/gcc.target/i386/stack-clash-protection.c validates the feature with `-fstack-clash-protection`. (5) gcc/common.opt defines `-fstack-clash-protection` at line 3054 as `Common Var(flag_stack_clash_protection) Optimization`.",
